TITLE: Redux Thunk Middleware Implementation with Annotations
DESCRIPTION: The actual implementation of the Redux thunk middleware with detailed annotations explaining how it works. This middleware intercepts function actions and calls them with dispatch and getState as arguments.
SOURCE: https://github.com/reduxjs/redux/blob/master/docs/usage/writing-logic-thunks.mdx#2025-04-07_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// standard middleware definition, with 3 nested functions:
// 1) Accepts `{dispatch, getState}`
// 2) Accepts `next`
// 3) Accepts `action`
const thunkMiddleware =
  ({ dispatch, getState }) =>
  next =>
  action => {
    // If the "action" is actually a function instead...
    if (typeof action === 'function') {
      // then call the function and pass `dispatch` and `getState` as arguments
      return action(dispatch, getState)
    }

    // Otherwise, it's a normal action - send it onwards
    return next(action)
  }
```

