TITLE: Implementing Reactive Logic with Redux-Saga in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create a saga that listens for a 'PING' action, waits for one second, and then dispatches a 'PONG' action using redux-saga.
SOURCE: https://github.com/reduxjs/redux/blob/master/docs/usage/migrating-to-modern-redux.mdx#2025-04-07_snippet_17

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { delay, put, takeEvery } from 'redux-saga/effects'

export function* ping() {
  yield delay(1000)
  yield put({ type: 'PONG' })
}

// "Watcher" saga that waits for a "signal" action, which is
// dispatched only to kick off logic, not to update state
export function* pingSaga() {
  yield takeEvery('PING', ping)
}
```

